session_1747386247614_ox25x5y: To what extent do you support or oppose upzoning policies that allow for higher density housing in traditionally single-family neighborhoods? Please explain your reasoning.
column3: I support upzoning policies in many areas because more people need affordable places to live, especially in this economy. So I do support upzoning policies for single-family neighborhoods because those are typically the people that need housing.

session_1747386247614_ox25x5y: What do you think are the most significant impacts, positive or negative, of increasing housing density in residential neighborhoods?
column3: I think the most positive impact is more affordable housing for more people. So more accessibility overall. I think the negative impact is overcrowding and having the overall environment altered. The views will change if a lot of skyscraper apartment complexes are built which is concerning. I love nature and love to feel connected to the environment and this might disrupt that connection.

session_1747386247614_ox25x5y: How do you think upzoning policies might affect housing affordability in urban areas?
column3: I think it will greatly decrease the prices and maybe value of the housing in urban areas

session_1747386247614_ox25x5y: What impact do you believe increased housing density might have on neighborhood character and quality of life?
column3: I think it may slighbtly lower quality of life if it removes the connection to nature. However if the sense of nature is preserved then I beluiebe the quality of life will improve for people. Cheaper rent, more shops being available and closer is good.

session_1747386247614_ox25x5y: How do you think upzoning might affect transportation systems and traffic congestion in cities?
column3: It will most likely increase traffic congestion for the general population. Unless there is more accessible and cheap public transportation. Then I think more people will take advantage of public transportation and traffic wont be changed.

session_1747386247614_ox25x5y: What role do you believe local government should play in regulating housing development and density?
column3: I believe that the local government should make sure there is enough accessible and affordable housing for the people that live there.

session_1747386247614_ox25x5y: How might environmental concerns factor into decisions about urban density and zoning?
column3: I think people who like to feel a sense of connection with nature will be against large buildings being built.

session_1747386247614_ox25x5y: What economic effects, both positive and negative, might result from changing zoning laws to allow more multi-family housing?
column3: I think it will have a positive impact on the economy because there will be more affordable housing. There will also be new shops build which will provide employment for some of the new people.

session_1747386247614_ox25x5y: How do you think the interests of current residents versus future residents should be balanced when making zoning decisions?
column3: I think current residents should have some say on what is going on in the community.

session_1747386247614_ox25x5y: What role do you think social equity and access to opportunity play in discussions about zoning and housing policy?
column3: I think increased social equity and decreased access will have a positive effect on zoning and housing discussions.
